<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="2d61a49e-a675-409d-81fb-2f30d9455aef" >

    <p>Our biomedical physics MSc and PhD programs provide advanced training in the complex interactions of the physical and biological worlds — at the intersection of physics and medicine. The curriculum equips students to meet the large demand for individuals skilled in applying physics-based concepts and methodologies to the diagnosis and treatment of illnesses.<br> <br> Our faculty members have strong ties to nearby world-class teaching hospitals, research institutes and cancer treatment centres. Experts from these organizations also serve as adjunct professors in the department, bringing expertise in areas such as medical imaging, radiation therapy, radiation protection and dosimetry.<br> Graduation is a pathway leading to challenging, impactful careers in a cutting-edge, multidisciplinary field. Our alumni enjoy a high employment rate within a few months, and have landed roles in research, academics, clinical medical physics, biomedical technology, or medical physics residency.</p>
    





</div>
